name: Florentine Bar & Restaurant.

reviews.review_text: Famous for their chicken cafreal. It was really good. we tried the Mixed fried rice, Chicken cafreal & Chicken xacutti. The food tasted good. The quantity was good. The atmosphere is ok. Also we have tried one Pinacolada cocktail, which tasted good. Their service is good, but a bit slow. Parking space is very limited. A small approach road leads to the restaurant.

Worst service. We go there around 10:30 at night, and the waiter on the first floor was complaining it is almost time for closing and asked us why we came at that time. We just ordered chicken cafreal, and four buns. He said they only have two and we agreed. Later another waiter came and throw 2 more buns to the basket like he gave for free. And he ask us to order drinks and we denied. Then he ask to my face, "why you come here just for this. No body comes here just for cafreal, you just wasted your time and our time." and he also commented how fast we finished our food. Worst experience ever in Goa.
A great authentic cozy very goa like ambience...good soul food...mus try and a favorite since years loved by locals is the chicken cafreal...the fry wet bombil and prawns chilly fry was yum...

description:
### Florentine Bar & Restaurant: A Goan Culinary Gem

Nestled in the scenic locale of Saligao, Florentine Bar & Restaurant captures the hearts and palates of locals and visitors alike, boasting an impressive overall rating of 4.2 from over 3,100 patrons. This charming eatery is particularly renowned for its specialties, notably the **chicken cafreal**, which dazzles taste buds with its aromatic profile and tender texture. Also featured prominently in reviews is the **chicken xacuti** and the beloved **poi**, which reflect the rich culinary heritage of Goa.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering Florentine Bar & Restaurant, guests are welcomed into a cozy, authentically Goan space that exudes warmth and charm. The d√©cor showcases local craftsmanship, with wooden accents and vibrant colors that evoke the lively spirit of the region. Lighting is soft and inviting, creating a casual yet intimate atmosphere perfect for savoring soul-satisfying dishes. Several customer images depict this inviting ambiance, featuring patrons enjoying their meals under cheerful lighting that enhances the restaurant's laid-back vibe. The overall feel resonates with comfort, making it a favored spot for locals to unwind.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Florentine offers a well-curated menu that pays homage to traditional Goan cuisine. The highlight, as repeatedly noted by diners, is the **chicken cafreal** (507 mentions), frequently lauded for its rich flavor and well-balanced spices. The **mixed fried rice** and the flavorful **prawn chilly fry** also come recommended, along with their homemade **serradura** dessert, which provides a sweet ending to a savory meal. Dietary options are available, ensuring that there is something for everyone, regardless of preference. Food presentation in customer-shared images showcases vibrant plates, enticing diners even before they take the first bite.

### Customer Experience & Service

While many reviews celebrate the quality of food, the service appears to be a point of contention. Though some patrons praise the staff for their friendliness and willingness to accommodate requests, others report a few less-than-stellar experiences concerning service speed and staff attitudes, particularly during late-night dining hours. For instance, one customer recounted an uncomfortable encounter with a waiter, highlighting potential inconsistencies in service during peak times. Despite these discrepancies, reviewers generally acknowledge that the restaurant maintains a welcoming environment, punctuated by the flavorful dishes that keep customers returning.

### Popularity & Reviews

This establishment has garnered a loyal following, often buzzing on social media as a go-to destination for authentic Goan fare. Many reviews emphasize the restaurant's local popularity, highlighting its enduring charm as a longstanding favorite. While no formal critic ratings or awards were mentioned, the sheer volume of positive feedback reinforces Florentine's well-deserved reputation in the community as a delightful culinary getaway.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The allure of Florentine is further captured in delightful images shared by patrons. From beautifully plated servings of chicken cafreal to the inviting ambiance of the restaurant, these photos encapsulate the essence of dining here. One striking image showcases a vibrant dish that perfectly illustrates the restaurant's commitment to flavorful authenticity, while others capture the cozy atmosphere that has made it a beloved spot for various occasions.

In summary, Florentine Bar & Restaurant is much more than a place to eat; it is a destination where the rich flavors of Goa intermingle with the warmth of its people. Visitors are sure to relish the well-prepared meals amidst a homey setting, while the occasional service hiccup doesn't detract from the overall fulfilling culinary experience. Consider stopping by to indulge in their chicken cafreal and enjoy the spirited vibe that consistently makes this restaurant a favorite in Saligao.
